@node tags
@chapter Processing @axml{} documents


The libraries under the @library{nausicaa xml tags ---} hierarchy
provide tools to manipulate @axml{} documents compliant with the
``Extensible Markup Language (@axml{}) 1.0 (Fifth Edition)'',
@acronym{W3C} Recommendation 26 November 2008@footnote{Find the document
and its errata at:

@center @url{http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/}
@center @url{http://www.w3.org/XML/xml-V10-5e-errata}}.  It is suggested to
import the libraries in this hiearchy with @code{xml.} as prefix:

@example
(import ---
  (prefix (nausicaa xml tags lexer)  xml.)
  (prefix (nausicaa xml tags parser) xml.))
@end example

@menu
* tags lexer::                  Tokenising @axml{} documents.
* tags parser::                 Parsing a stream of @axml{} tokens.
* tags fixed-strings::          A collection of common strings.
@end menu

